Since the 0.2 version, you can generate unit tests for services with the "Spock Framework":https://code.google.com/p/spock/ using the [create-unit-test-service-spock|Scripts] command:
{code}
grails create-unit-test-service-spock [domainClass]
{code}
Tou will get the following unit test files:
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListMaxSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListOffsetSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListSortOrderSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceCreateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceUpdateSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceGetSpec.groovy@
* @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceDeleteSpec.groovy@
You can generate each file with the following commands:
{table}
 *File* | *Command*
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-list-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListMaxSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-list-max-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListOffsetSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-list-offset-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceListSortOrderSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-list-sort-order-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceCreateSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-create-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceUpdateSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-update-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceGetSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-get-spock|Scripts]
 @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceDeleteSpec.groovy@ | [create-unit-test-service-delete-spock|Scripts]
{table}
If we open the @test/unit/mypackage/PersonServiceCreateSpec.groovy@ file, we will find something like this:
{code}
package mypackage

import grails.test.mixin.*
import spock.lang.*

@TestFor(PersonService)
@Mock(Person)
class PersonServiceCreateSpec extends Specification {

    def "test ok"() {

        when:
            def instance = PersonMock.mock( 0 )
            service.create( instance )
        then:
            Person.count() == 1

    }

    def "test Person null"() {

        when:
            def instance = null
            service.create( instance )
        then:
            IllegalArgumentException e = thrown()
            e.message == "Parameter 'person' is null"

    }

    def "test Person invalid"() {

        when:
            def instance = PersonMock.mock( 0 )
            instance.name = name
            service.create( instance )
        then:
            IllegalArgumentException e = thrown()
            e.message == "Parameter 'person' is invalid"
        where:
            name = null

    }

}
{code}
{note}
For versions of Grails prior to 2.3.0, you need to install the "Grails Spock Plugin":http://grails.org/plugin/spock if you want to execute the tests.
{note}
